title: Feminist AI at PyConDE 2026
---
author: ORGANIZERS
---
pub_date: 2025-03-22
---
body:

![Logo](logo-femministic-ai.png)

We’re excited to announce that [Feminist AI](https://feministai.party/) will be joining us again at **PyConDE & PyData 2026** in **Darmstadt**!

The **Feminist AI LAN Party** is from **Tuesday, April 14th to Thursday, April 16th,
2026** — and you're invited!

**No conference ticket? No problem!**  
If you're not attending the main conference, you can still join the LAN party by requesting a **special badge** at the registration desk.
Just let them know you'd like to attend the Feminist AI LAN Party. 
Please note this does not include access to any other parts of the conference.

📍 **Location:** darmstadtium, room 3.05 Radon, during open hours:

- **Tuesday, April 14:** 11:30 – 16:00
- **Wednesday, April 15:** 10:00 – 16:00
- **Thursday, April 16:** 10:00 – 15:00

🎮 **What to expect:**  

Coding never stops at the LAN Party! Drop in for hands-on sessions like:

- Data Annotation
- Hacking LLMs
- Building a FeministLLM

For full details, visit: [Feminist AI LAN Party](https://feministai.party/events/2025-04-23)

**Happy Coding!**